(27, 193, 'Stephen Doane', 'scdoane@cox.net', '', '68.226.138.46', '2013-11-24 16:42:11', '2013-11-24 16:42:11', 'I have a recipe to share. This is a veggie omelet which I developed to replace my old, daily bacon &amp; eggs breakfast. \r\n\r\nchopped veggies: i green onion, 1 tbsp (or more,) red bell pepper (raw or grilled,) 1 tbsp fresh or canned mushrooms, 1/2 tsp minced garlic.\r\nEgg Beaters (1 cup)\r\n1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese or grated parmesan.\r\n2 tbsp olive oil.\r\n\r\nIn a 9" skillet:\r\nSautee veggies in olive oil ''till tender. Add minced garlic near end of sauteeing to avoid burning it.\r\nPour Egg Beaters around and over veggies.\r\nAdd shredded or crumbled cheese and lower heat. Cover to contain heat (helps cook top and melt cheese.) I use an inverted pie pan or aluminum foil. Check frequently to avoid over-cooking.\r\nCook just until top solidifies and cheese melts. Fold and serve.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/31.0.1650.57 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
(28, 193, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '74.80.16.86', '2013-11-25 15:51:23', '2013-11-25 15:51:23', 'Thank you for sharing! Will post this on the blog for everyone to see. Sounds very good. :)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/6.0)', '', 27, 2),
(16, 59, 'Daniel F. Adams', 'danieladams25@att.net', 'http://gogel', '98.183.89.64', '2013-11-06 11:25:15', '2013-11-06 11:25:15', 'need instruction on how to do exercicese', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/30.0.1599.101 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
(17, 59, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '184.184.200.119', '2013-11-06 15:47:07', '2013-11-06 15:47:07', 'Good morning Mr. Adams-\nIf you click on the Ba Duan Jin Step by Step Instructions in my blog (where you left this message)it will come up and give you another link to click on under the title that will download the instructions with illustrations. it says "Ba Duan Jin instructions 1-4 with illustrations".', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/6.0)', '', 16, 2),
(20, 193, 'andy', 'andyfalls12@bellsouth.net', '', '23.125.144.96', '2013-11-12 20:55:55', '2013-11-12 20:55:55', 'My biggest problem is excersise,,,,my second problem is menus.  I can only cook veggies so many ways. I am still having problems getting enough protein......', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/6.0)', '', 0, 0),
(21, 193, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '184.184.200.119', '2013-11-13 16:18:25', '2013-11-13 16:18:25', 'Good morning Mr. Falls. Check out the free exercise videos you can do at home that were shared with another participant in the program in my blog. Simple walking is beneficial. Listen to your favorite music to pass the time more quickly or take a friend with you. Also, there is a recipe book entitled " Everyday cooking with Dean Ornish" that may be of help to you. I bought it on amazon for $3. Hope this helps!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/6.0)', '', 20, 2),
(65, 120, 'kenneth Miller', 'blacklmare@cox.net', '', '70.189.51.119', '2014-02-25 00:41:20', '2014-02-25 00:41:20', 'Started regiment in August ...my average nutrition score is 1.75 per week. I eat no meat all vegitables, fruit, egg beaters and 100% whole grain bread...my highest score is Coffee and Fish.\r\n\r\nWorkout 6 days a week (Strength and Cardio) and walk 30-40 mins on Sunday.  Workouts are 60-80 min on Monday Wed and Friday, 40 min workouts with 20 of that cardio, on Tues, Thurs and Saturday. Meditate as well as I can for 30 + mins every day.\r\n\r\nMy blood pressure is still 140/80 avg, blood sugar is around 110 no change.. There has been no noticeable changes in my weight after losing about 7-8 pounds in the first month or so.  I am stronger and have more endurance....(I am however taking a testosterone lowering drug that affects all of my issues, from weight gain to high blood pressure.)\r\n\r\nmy main concern has always been my cholesterol and my blood flow.....We will see if there has been improvement on April 20.....Peace', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/33.0.1750.117 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
(67, 120, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '74.80.16.86', '2014-02-26 16:39:38', '2014-02-26 16:39:38', 'Mr. Miller- Sounds like you are doing awesome! Can''t wait to see your numbers either. \nDr. Patience McCoy', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko', '', 65, 2),
(81, 120, 'kenneth Miller', 'blacklmare@cox.net', '', '68.226.155.254', '2014-04-16 14:53:48', '2014-04-16 14:53:48', 'Got my numbers on Monday...blood sugar is up  all others are basically the same except for Trigs, it was dowm from about 100 avg to 77.......Not anything to write home about.....What next?   Think I will ever grow new arteries?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/33.0.1750.152 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
(83, 120, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '74.80.16.86', '2014-04-16 15:45:59', '2014-04-16 15:45:59', 'Good morning Mr. Miller. I just received your labs and I think you had a great improvement compared to last August! You have dropped your Total cholesterol 55pts (25% reduction), LDL 23pts (20% reduction) and Triglycerides 92pts (51% reduction)! That is awesome with just diet and exercise! You should be very proud of yourself.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko', '', 81, 2),
(84, 193, 'Tannia', 'tanniaf@gmail.com', '', '184.187.147.229', '2014-04-17 20:59:15', '2014-04-17 20:59:15', 'I have found that the best encouragement tool to keep me motivated is a little device that clips to my waistband called a Fitbit One.  It tracks steps, distance in miles, calories burned, stairs climbed and quality of sleep.  It has an app for your smartphone and also comes with a little toggle that goes into you computer that makes the information from the device connect through your wifi also.   All information is then logged into your own webpage which is private on Fitbit.com.  There you can also log your food intake and weight and any other useful information.  I started out setting my goal to walk a minimum of 10,000 steps a day and or at least 4 miles.  But since I have started wearing it I am so motivated by it that I usually walk between 8 to 15 miles a day, most of the time just doing laps around my pool and in my yard or house in bad weather.  I even sleep with it so if I wake up at night to walk to the bathroom those steps count too, every step counts.   I started wearing this following cervical surgery weight gain in Jan. 2014 and it only 3 months I have dropped 25 lbs and that is doing it the healthy way.  Eating healthy and lots of walking.  This is the first time I have ever dieted the healthy way so I am really excited that I was introduced to this website and "The Spectrum" book.  I just started the book and look forward to learning even more about healthy eating and living and hoping to change my lifestyle ways for the better.   Thank you to Dr. Chen and his wonderful staff and to Pam, my ECP specialist for the encouragement and information and  for welcoming me to this website.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64; Trident/5.0; BOIE9;ENUS)', '', 0, 0),
(85, 193, 'Patience McCoy', 'drpmccoy@gmail.com', '', '74.80.16.86', '2014-04-24 15:47:31', '2014-04-24 15:47:31', 'Awesome! thanks for sharing!\nDr. McCoy', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko', '', 84, 2),
(114, 66, 'Robert Broussard', 'bonorm@cox.net', '', '174.64.176.104', '2014-08-19 00:46:47', '2014-08-19 00:46:47', 'I walk 3 times a week for at least an hour. Distance is 4.75 miles in 66 minutes. Total steps around 9730. Hope this will make up for 30 minute a day.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; Trident/7.0; MDDCJS; rv:11.0) like Gecko', '', 0, 0),
(119, 66, 'Robert Broussard', 'bonorm@cox.net', '', '174.64.176.104', '2014-08-22 16:04:44', '2014-08-22 16:04:44', 'I need some help with my blood sugar count. I eat group 1 and 2 foods. I take metformin after I eat breakfast. I measure my blood glucose after I get back from my exercise, 20 minutes cool down first. My glucose is always high, 205-275. Any thoughts on how I can overcome the high glucose levels. Thanks', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; Trident/7.0; MDDCJS; rv:11.0) like Gecko', '', 0, 0);
