(49, 2, '2013-08-28 15:24:58', '2013-08-28 15:24:58', '<b><i><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Jin in Chinese means something brilliant and beautiful</span></i></b>\r\n\r\n<span>Ba Duan Jin is a group of Chinese stretches that has been around for hundreds of years, being perfected over the years so that it can be used for all age groups. It broken down into eight separate stretches, each focusing on a different physical areas. It has been proven to help with relaxation/stress management and even health issues. </span>\r\n\r\nTwo Hands Hold up the Heavens<b> -</b><span> Center the body.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Drawing the Bow to Shoot the Hawk (or Vulture)- </span><span>Focus on the kidneys and spleen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Separate Heaven and Earth- S</span><span>timulate the stomach.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Wise Owl Gazes Backwards or Look Back-</span><span> Stretch the neck.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Sway the Head and Shake the Tail- R</span><span>egulate the function of the heart and lungs. </span>\r\n\r\n<span>Two Hands Hold the Feet-  Strengthen the kidneys and waist.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Clench the Fists and Glare Fiercely-</span><span> Increases general vitality and muscular strength.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Bouncing on the Toes-</span><span> said to "smooth out" the qi after practice of the preceding seven pieces.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'BaDuan Jin health benefits', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baduan-jin-health-benefits', '', '', '2013-08-29 16:07:19', '2013-08-29 16:07:19', '', 0, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=49', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(61, 2, '2013-08-26 16:43:37', '2013-08-26 16:43:37', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>The Ba duan jin as a whole is broken down into eight separate exercises, each focusing on a different physical areas.  The Ba duan jin can be done either standing or seated if medically necessary.</span>\r\n\r\nTwo Hands Hold up the Heavens<b> -</b><span> Center the body.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Drawing the Bow to Shoot the Hawk (or Vulture)- </span><span>Focus on the kidneys and spleen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Separate Heaven and Earth- s</span><span>timulate the stomach.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Wise Owl Gazes Backwards or Look Back-</span><span> stretch the neck.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Sway the Head and Shake the Tail- </span><span>regulate the function of the heart and lungs. </span>\r\n\r\n<span>Two Hands Hold the Feet-  Strengthen the Kidneys and Waist</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Clench the Fists and Glare Fiercely-</span><span> aimed at increasing general vitality and muscular strength.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Bouncing on the Toes-</span><span> said to "smooth out" the qi after practice of the preceding seven pieces.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'BaDuan Jin health benefits', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '49-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-26 16:43:37', '2013-08-26 16:43:37', '', 49, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=61', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
