(284, 2, '2013-11-25 16:16:42', '2013-11-25 16:16:42', 'I have a recipe to share. This is a veggie omelet which I developed to replace my old, daily bacon &amp; eggs breakfast.\r\n\r\nchopped veggies: i green onion, 1 tbsp (or more,) red bell pepper (raw or grilled,) 1 tbsp fresh or canned mushrooms, 1/2 tsp minced garlic. Egg Beaters (1 cup) 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese or grated parmesan. 2 tbsp olive oil.\r\n\r\nIn a 9″ skillet: Sautee veggies in olive oil ’till tender. Add minced garlic near end of sauteeing to avoid burning it. Pour Egg Beaters around and over veggies. Add shredded or crumbled cheese and lower heat. Cover to contain heat (helps cook top and melt cheese.) I use an inverted pie pan or aluminum foil. Check frequently to avoid over-cooking. Cook just until top solidifies and cheese melts. Fold and serve.', 'From Stephen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'from-stephen', '', '', '2013-11-25 16:16:51', '2013-11-25 16:16:51', '', 169, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?post_type=topic&#038;p=284', 0, 'topic', '', 0),
