r.</i></b> Prayer is the best known and most widely practiced example of meditation. Spoken and written prayers are found in most faith traditions. You can pray using your own words or read prayers written by others. .\r\n\r\n<b><i>Read and reflect.</i></b> Many people report that they benefit from reading poems or sacred texts, and taking a few moments to quietly reflect on their meaning. You also can listen to sacred music.', 'Relaxation/Meditation and Stress Management Ideas', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '610-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-25 15:37:58', '2014-08-25 15:37:58', '', 610, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=656', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(758, 2, '2014-10-16 15:56:11', '2014-10-16 15:56:11', '***I just wanted to drop a little note about the program I was on and to let you know how I am coming along.<span style="font-family: Arial;">A year later I still am doing the areobics 3 to 5 times a week.  I still meditate daily and I do the yoga stretching just about daily.  I don''t miss many days of that. </span><span style="font-family: Arial;">I still walk, weather permitting, 30 minutes a day. My medication is still greatly reduced from when I started this last year. I am down size wise from a 22W to a ladies size 14/16. From JS</span>\r\n\r\n***Cholesterol Results for Mr. M. Total Cholesterol went from 155 to 91; a 40% decrease! Triglycerides went from 77 to 56; a 28% decrease! and LDL went from 106 to 51; a 52% decrease! Excellent job!! Congrats!\r\n\r\n****Results for Mr. B. after 3 months:  Lost 11lbs, BP down from 148/84 to 120/62, Triglycerides significantly improved from 256 to 132, Glucose levels from 160 to 107.\r\n\r\nMr. B. has had trouble managing his diabetes with prescription medication for 20 years but within 3 shorts months of following the website, he is finally able to cut down on his diabetes medication.  His inspiring success story involves eating more vegetables and fruit, eliminating white bread, white rice, and white potatoes, appropriate portion sizes of protein with each meal, and a regular exercise routine.  Mr. B. admits it was a little difficult in the beginning to change his eating habits but he was armed with will power.  Now that he can feel and see a tremendous change, he will never go back! Congratulations!!\r\n\r\n***Results for Mr. H. after 3 months: Lost 15 lbs.  BP down 144/83 to 102/64. Cholesterol significantly improved: Total cholesterol 283 down to 195; Triglycerides 356 down to 128; LDL 178 down to 128. EXCELLENT!!\r\n\r\n***Mr. M. has had a great improvement in his cholesterol when compared to last August! He has dropped his Total cholesterol 55pts (25% reduction), LDL 23pts (20% reduction) and Triglycerides 92pts (51% reduction)! That is awesome with just diet and exercise! You should be very proud of yourself.\r\n\r\n***Mrs. S. has also had an excellent improvement in her cholesterol from September! She has dropped her TC 40pts (17% reduction), Triglycerides 56pts (35% reduction), LDL 36pts (36% reduction) and increased her HDL 7pts! Awesome!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Encouraging Patient Results', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '120-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-16 15:56:11', '2014-10-16 15:56:11', '', 120, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=758', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
