(1297, 2, '2019-09-12 19:52:33', '2019-09-12 19:52:33', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To understand how the right foods can help you after exercise, it''s important to understand how your body is affected by physical activity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you''re working out, your muscles use up their glycogen stores for fuel. This results in your muscles being partially depleted of glycogen. Some of the proteins in your muscles also get broken down and damaged.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After your workout, your body tries to rebuild its glycogen stores and repair and regrow those muscle proteins.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eating the right nutrients soon after you exercise can help your body get this done faster. It is particularly important to eat carbs and protein after your workout and drink plenty of water to rehydrate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing this helps your body:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Decrease muscle protein breakdown.</li><li>Increase muscle protein synthesis (growth).</li><li>Restore glycogen stores.</li><li>Enhance recovery.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>healthline.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Eating after a Workout is Important', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'eating-after-a-workout-is-important__trashed', '', '', '2019-10-09 15:35:03', '2019-10-09 15:35:03', '', 0, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=1297', 0, 'post', '', 0),
