(1311, 2, '2019-12-04 21:35:17', '2019-12-04 21:35:17', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ingredients: Serves 4-6</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the roasted squash:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 medium butternut\nsquash, peeled, seeded and cut into 1-inch cubes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 Tablespoons\nolive oil</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 teaspoon salt</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1/2 teaspoon\nfreshly cracked black pepper</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the stuffing:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4 Tablespoons\nunsalted butter</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 large shallots,\npeeled and thinly sliced</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 celery stalks,\nthinly sliced</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4 garlic cloves,\nfinely grated</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5 fresh sage\nleaves, minced</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1/2 teaspoon dried\nthyme</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 1/3 cups wild\nrice</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4 cups chicken or\nvegetable broth</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; salt and pepper</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1/4 cup lightly\ntoasted pecans, roughly chopped</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1/3 cup fresh\nparsley, finely chopped</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Toss the cubed\nsquash, olive oil, salt and pepper together and spread in an even layer on a\nbaking sheet. Roast for 25 minutes or until fork tender. Set aside.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. In a large pot or pan with tall sides (that has a lid)\nmelt the butter over a medium-high flame. Add the sliced shallots and sauté\nuntil soft and lightly caramelized. Then add the sliced celery and finely\ngrated (or minced) garlic. Sauté until soft and fragrant (about 3 minutes).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Add the wild rice, broth and a pinch of salt and pepper.\nStir well and bring to a boil. Allow the liquid to boil for 5 minutes,\nuncovered.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Reduce the flame to a simmer, cover and cook for 40-50\nminutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid is fully absorbed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Once the rice is fully cooked, fold in the roasted\nsquash, chopped pecans and parsley. Toss to coat, taste and adjust seasoning to\nyour liking and serve.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Toss the cubed\nsquash, olive oil, salt and pepper together and spread in an even layer on a\nbaking sheet. Roast for 25 minutes or until fork tender. Set aside.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a large pot or pan with tall sides (that has a lid) melt\nthe butter over a medium-high flame. Add the sliced shallots and sauté until\nsoft and lightly caramelized. Then add the sliced celery and finely grated (or\nminced) garlic. Sauté until soft and fragrant (about three minutes).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Add the wild rice, broth and a pinch of salt and pepper.\nStir well and bring to a boil. Allow the liquid to boil for five minutes,\nuncovered.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reduce the flame to a simmer, cover and cook for 40-50\nminutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid is fully absorbed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the rice is fully cooked, fold in the roasted squash,\nchopped pecans and parsley. Toss to coat, taste and adjust seasoning to your\nliking and serve. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Butternut Squash and Wild Rice Stuffing', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'butternut-squash-and-wild-rice-stuffing__trashed', '', '', '2020-01-20 18:08:07', '2020-01-20 18:08:07', '', 0, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=1311', 0, 'post', '', 0),
