(1337, 2, '2020-03-16 19:12:00', '2020-03-16 19:12:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What''s the difference between a\nbacterial infection and a viral infection?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Viral or\nbacterial, it''s never fun to have an infection. But knowing the difference\nbetween the two can be the best way to get better. While bacteria and viruses\ncan both cause mild to serious infections, they are different from each other.\nThis is important to understand, because bacterial and viral infections must be\ntreated differently. The most important distinction between bacteria and\nviruses is that antibiotic drugs usually kill bacteria, but they aren''t\neffective against viruses. Misusing antibiotics to treat viral infections leads\nto the problem of antibiotic resistance. Which means when you actually need an\nantibiotic- it won’t work as effectively anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both viral\nand bacterial infections are spread in similar ways:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Coughing and sneezing</li><li>Contact with infected people, especially through kissing or sharing drinks</li><li>Contact with contaminated surfaces, food, and water</li><li>Contact with infected creatures, including pets, livestock, and insects like fleas and ticks</li><li>There are several non-prescription drug measures you can try for relief of your symptoms. Besides getting alot of rest of drinking alot of fluids, here are some other suggestions.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Common Cold:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Use a cool mist humidifier or vaporizer</li><li>Avoid smoking, secondhand smoke, and\nother pollutants</li><li>Take nonprescription meds like\nacetaminophen or ibuprofen to relieve pain or fever</li><li>Use saline nasal spray for congestion</li><li>Use honey for a cough</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sore Throat:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Ice chips, sore throat spray,\npopsicles, or lozenges</li><li>Gargle with salt water</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sinus Pain/Pressure:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>A warm compress over the nose and\nforehead can help relieve sinus pressure</li><li>Take a steam shower to break up sinus\ncongestion</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Viral vs Bacterial Infections', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'viral-vs-bacterial-infections__trashed', '', '', '2020-06-01 16:58:33', '2020-06-01 16:58:33', '', 0, 'http://www.drjchen.com/blog/?p=1337', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1338, 2, '2020-03-16 19:12:00', '2020-03-16 19:12:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What''s the difference between a\nbacterial infection and a viral infection?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Viral or\nbacterial, it''s never fun to have an infection. But knowing the difference\nbetween the two can be the best way to get better. While bacteria and viruses\ncan both cause mild to serious infections, they are different from each other.\nThis is important to understand, because bacterial and viral infections must be\ntreated differently. The most important distinction between bacteria and\nviruses is that antibiotic drugs usually kill bacteria, but they aren''t\neffective against viruses. Misusing antibiotics to treat viral infections leads\nto the problem of antibiotic resistance. Which means when you actually need an\nantibiotic- it won’t work as effectively anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both viral\nand bacterial infections are spread in similar ways:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Coughing and sneezing</li><li>Contact with infected people, especially through kissing or sharing drinks</li><li>Contact with contaminated surfaces, food, and water</li><li>Contact with infected creatures, including pets, livestock, and insects like fleas and ticks</li><li>There are several non-prescription drug measures you can try for relief of your symptoms. Besides getting alot of rest of drinking alot of fluids, here are some other suggestions.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Common Cold:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Use a cool mist humidifier or vaporizer</li><li>Avoid smoking, secondhand smoke, and\nother pollutants</li><li>Take nonprescription meds like\nacetaminophen or ibuprofen to relieve pain or fever</li><li>Use saline nasal spray for congestion</li><li>Use honey for a cough</li></ul>\n<!-- /